The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms, specifically related to treewidth, brambles, and minors. These topics are commonly studied in computer science sub-categories such as Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
